
### Explanation of Additional Configuration

- **functions**: This section allows you to specify settings for your serverless functions. The `maxDuration` property sets the maximum execution time for your PHP functions, which can help prevent long-running processes from timing out.

Make sure to test your deployment after adding this configuration to ensure everything works as expected. ```json
{
  "version": 2,
  "builds": [
    {
      "src": "api/*.php",
      "use": "@vercel/php"
    }
  ],
  "routes": [
    {
      "src": "/(.*)",
      "dest": "api/$1"
    }
  ],
  "env": {
    "DATABASE_URL": "postgresql://neondb_owner:npg_y3fzF1kdcTxM@ep-spring-butterfly-a5f6zfko-pooler.us-east-2.aws.neon.tech/neondb?sslmode=require"
  },
  "functions": {
    "api/*.php": {
      "maxDuration": 10
    }
  },
  "static": {
    "directory": "public"
  }
}
